%5Cn%3Cp%3ECountries%20need%20to%20cut%20emissions%20by%2028%20per%20cent%20to%20limit%20global%20warming%20to%202%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20by%2042%20per%20cent%20to%20meet%20the%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20goal%2C%20United%20Nations%20Environment%20Programme's%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%202023%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BBroken%20Record%26quot%3B%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20released%20ahead%20of%20the%2028th%20session%20of%20the%20annual%20UN%20climate%20talks%20or%20COP28%20in%20Dubai%20said%20global%20emissions%20rose%20by%201.2%20per%20cent%20in%202021-2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFully%20implementing%20efforts%20implied%20by%20unconditional%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%20(NDCs)%20would%20put%20the%20world%20on%20track%20for%20limiting%20temperature%20rise%20to%202.9%20degrees%20Celsius.%20Conditional%20NDCs%20fully%20implemented%20would%20lead%20to%20temperatures%20not%20exceeding%202.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20countries%20agreed%20to%20hold%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20global%20average%20temperature%20to%20well%20below%202%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20pursue%20efforts%20to%20limit%20the%20temperature%20increase%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20countries%20have%20made%20progress%20in%20reducing%20greenhouse%20gas%20(GHG)%20emissions%20since%20the%20signing%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20as%20the%202016%20edition%20of%20the%20report%20had%20a%20projected%20warming%20of%20up%20to%203.4%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20a%20business-as-usual%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20progress%2C%20the%20world%20is%20very%20far%20from%20limiting%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20to%20avoid%20extreme%2C%20destructive%20and%20likely%20irreversible%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20the%20UN%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20is%20already%20experiencing%20unprecedented%20heat%2C%20floods%2C%20wildfires%2C%20cyclones%2C%20and%20droughts%20at%20just%201.1%20degrees%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20the%20beginning%20of%20October%2C%2086%20days%20in%20this%20year%20were%20recorded%20with%20temperatures%20over%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels.%20September%20was%20the%20hottest%20recorded%20month%20ever%2C%20with%20global%20average%20temperatures%201.8%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20it%20is%20still%20possible%20to%20make%20the%201.5%20degree%20limit%20a%20reality.%20It%20requires%20tearing%20out%20the%20poisoned%20root%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%3A%20fossil%20fuels.%20And%20it%20demands%20a%20just%2C%20equitable%20renewables%20transition%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ant%C3%B2nio%20Guterres%2C%20Secretary-General%20of%20the%20UN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20calls%20for%20all%20nations%20to%20deliver%20economy-wide%2C%20low-carbon%20development%20transformations%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20energy%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20coal%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20extracted%20over%20the%20lifetime%20of%20producing%20and%20the%20planned%20mines%20and%20fields%20would%20emit%20more%20than%20three-and-a-half%20times%20the%20carbon%20budget%20available%20to%20limit%20warming%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20almost%20the%20entire%20budget%20available%20for%202%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20science%20defines%20carbon%20budget%20as%20the%20amount%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20that%20can%20be%20emitted%20for%20a%20given%20level%20of%20global%20warming%20(1.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20this%20case).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloped%20countries%20have%20already%20consumed%20more%20than%2080%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20global%20carbon%20budget%2C%20leaving%20countries%20like%20India%20with%20very%20little%20carbon%20space%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCountries%20with%20greater%20capacity%20and%20responsibility%20for%20emissions%20--%20particularly%20high-income%20and%20high-emitting%20countries%20among%20the%20G20%20--%20will%20need%20to%20take%20more%20ambitious%20and%20rapid%20action%20and%20provide%20financial%20and%20technical%20support%20to%20developing%20nations.%20As%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20already%20account%20for%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20global%20GHG%20emissions%2C%20meeting%20development%20needs%20with%20low-emissions%20growth%20is%20a%20priority%20in%20such%20nations%20--%20such%20as%20addressing%20energy%20demand%20patterns%20and%20prioritising%20clean%20energy%20supply%20chains%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarjeet%20Singh%2C%20the%20head%20of%20global%20political%20strategy%20at%20the%20New%20Delhi-based%20Climate%20Action%20Network%20International%2C%20said%20the%20world%20is%20on%20thin%20ice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stark%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20projected%20emissions%20from%20coal%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20extraction%20are%20on%20track%20to%20exceed%20the%20carbon%20budget%20needed%20to%20limit%20warming%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20by%20more%20than%20three-and-a-half%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700547180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-01%2Ftmdcpefo_global-warming-generic_625x300_02_January_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fworld-headed-for-nearly-3-degrees-warming-if-steps-not-taken-un-report-4590603%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20world%20is%20headed%20for%20a%20temperature%20rise%20of%20around%203%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%